## KUBERNETES MULTI-POD — DATA PROTECTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CRITICAL: Multiple pods share session state. ASP.NET Core Data Protection
keys MUST be stored in Redis, not the local file system.

In both Flagly.Web/Program.cs and Flagly.Api/Program.cs:

  builder.Services.AddDataProtection()
    .PersistKeysToStackExchangeRedis(
        ConnectionMultiplexer.Connect(redisConnectionString),
        "Flagly:DataProtection:Keys")
    .SetApplicationName("Flagly")
    .SetDefaultKeyLifetime(TimeSpan.FromDays(90));

This ensures all pods encrypt/decrypt session cookies with the same keys.
Without this, users are logged out when load balancer routes to a different pod.

NuGet required: Microsoft.AspNetCore.DataProtection.StackExchangeRedis

Session cookie config:
  builder.Services.ConfigureApplicationCookie(opts => {
    opts.LoginPath = "/account/login";
    opts.ExpireTimeSpan = TimeSpan.FromHours(8);
    opts.SlidingExpiration = true;
    opts.Cookie.SecurePolicy = CookieSecurePolicy.Always;
    opts.Cookie.SameSite = SameSiteMode.Lax;
    opts.Cookie.Name = "flagly.auth";
  });

