## AUDIT LOGGING — SERVICE IMPLEMENTATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

IAuditLogService / AuditLogService in Flagly.Application/Services/

All write operations in FeatureFlagService, EnvironmentService,
UserGroupService, CompanyGroupService, AdminService MUST call
IAuditLogService to record the change WITHIN the same transaction.

Pattern: services call uow.AuditLogs.Add(new AuditLog { ... })
then uow.SaveChangesAsync() — single commit covers both the change + the log.

AuditLogService provides helper methods:
  Task LogFlagActionAsync(AuditAction action, FeatureFlag flag,
      ProjectEnvironment env, string performedByUserId, string performedByName,
      string ip, object? prev = null, object? next = null);
      
  Task LogAdminActionAsync(AuditAction action, string targetEntityId,
      string targetEntityName, string performedByUserId,
      string performedByName, string ip,
      object? prev = null, object? next = null);
      
  Task LogProjectActionAsync(AuditAction action, Project project,
      string performedByUserId, string performedByName, string ip,
      string? envName = null, object? prev = null, object? next = null);

PreviousValueJson / NewValueJson: serialize only the changed fields
(not the entire entity) using System.Text.Json to keep logs readable.

Example for FlagTargetingUpdated:
  prev: { "targetMode": "Everyone" }
  next: { "targetMode": "Company", "companyGroupId": "...", "companyGroupName": "Enterprise Clients" }

ICurrentUserService:
  string UserId { get; }
  string UserName { get; }
  string IpAddress { get; }
  (Implemented via IHttpContextAccessor)

